4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would establish a program at Marion
6 Military Institute that would confer a degree and
7 provide the necessary basic curriculum for individuals
8 to become certified law enforcement officers in the
9 State of Alabama.
10 This bill would require that the commission
11 grant individuals who graduate from the institute's
12 program provisional certification as Alabama law
13 enforcement officers, provided that the individual is
14 hired by an Alabama law enforcement agency within the
15 prescribed provisional time period.
16
17
18 A BILL
19 TO BE ENTITLED
20 AN ACT
21
22 Relating to Marion Military Institute; to add Sections
23 16-60-340 and 36-21-46.1 to the Code of Alabama 1975; to
24 establish a program at Marion Military Institute that would
25 provide the necessary education and training for graduates to
26 become certified law enforcement officers in the State of
27 Alabama; and to require that the commission grant provisional
28 certification to graduates of the program.
